// An IMPLICIT move (a bare move-only opaque handed to a consuming `own` param — no `move` keyword)
// must consume the source so its RAII auto-drop is suppressed. Otherwise the file is closed TWICE:
// once by the explicit `io.fclose(f)` call and again by the scope-exit auto-drop. The transfer is
// made explicit in the HIR during lowering (semantic flags it, lowering materializes `move`), so
// codegen has a single move path — the user's `main` must emit EXACTLY ONE `io.fclose` call.
// (The dtor symbol is `@io.fclose` whole-program, or `@arche.io.fclose` under per-unit mangling — the
// regex matches either; what matters is EXACTLY ONE call.)
// RUN: %arche build --emit llvm-ir -o %t.ll %s ; test $(awk '/define .*@main_user/{f=1} f&&/call void @(arche\.)?io\.fclose\(/{c++} f&&/^}/{print c+0;exit}' %t.ll) -eq 1
#import { io }
main :: proc() {
  io.fopen_read("/dev/null")(f:);
  io.fclose(f);
}
